    "where n is the total number of sentences in the document, emb(•) is the embedding function, and λ is a hyperparameter.",
    "When λ = 0, the chunker operates purely based on semantic similarity; when λ = 1, it mirrors the Fixed-size Chunker.",
    "(3), a cosine similarity of 0 indicates orthogonal (unrelated) sentence embeddings, while negative cosine similarity values are treated as 0, as they do not aid in retrieval or generation.",
    "Without losing generality, we employed singlelinkage agglomerative clustering and DBSCAN (Ester et al., 1996) as representatives of clustering algorithms.",
    "Further details on these methods an their adjustments during experimentation are provided in Appendix A."
